{"key":"post-12448424","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12448424</id>\n<content>Autoclaves are generally not suitable for our purposes.&amp;nbsp; Most autoclaves are set up to dump pressure at the end of the cycle.&amp;nbsp; This results in a massive and sudden loss of pressure, which also takes ALL of the moisture out too.&amp;nbsp; This is great for the CIA torture facilities. . .Oops, I meant instruments that dentists commonly use, but will ruin the moisture content of your jars.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We use pressure cookers, not autoclaves for mushroom grains and substrates.&amp;nbsp; If you don't have a regular pressure cooker that will cool slowly and remain sealed, you'll want to stick to the brf tek where you can sterilize in a large pot with a tight fitting lid.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12448445</next>\n<prev>12448371</prev>\n<first>12442991</first>\n<last>12462315</last>\n<when>1272123310</when>\n<utime>04/24/10 06:35 PM</utime>\n</post>"}